<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Macao </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Macao-Taipa Bridge Goes Into Operation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1002142394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1402 GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1002142394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Macao, February 10 (XINHUA) -- The new Macao-Taipa 
bridge went into operation here today. 
  Macao Governor General Vasco Joaquim Rocha Vieira presided 
over a ceremony marking the opening of the bridge. 
  The governor first expressed his congratulations on the 
completion of the new bridge, saying he was convinced that the 
bridge would bring great benefits to local people. 
  The new bridge is expected to ease the tense traffic in 
Macao, the governor said. 
  He added that the opening of the bridge is a recognition of 
the great efforts that technicians and builders have made to 
finish the project. 
  It is learned that starting from today, all heavy-duty 
trucks 
will not be allowed to use the old Macao-Taipa bridge, finished 
in 1974. 
  The four-lane new bridge is 4,414 meters long and 19.3 
meters 
wide, with a total 1108.86-meter bridge approach at the two ends. 
  Construction of the bridge, started in 1990, costed more 
than 
600 million Macao patacas (about 77 million U.S. dollars). 

</TEXT>

