<F P=100> TAIWAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Premier Hears Report on Handling of Radioactive Steel </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1502061094 Taipei China Broadcasting Corporation News 
Network in Mandarin 2300 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1502061094 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei China Broadcasting Corporation News 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Hookup" program] </F>
  [Text] After hearing a brief report yesterday [8 February] 
by (Hsu I-ming), chairman of the Atomic Energy Council under the 
Executive Yuan, on procedures for the handling of buildings 
affected by radioactive steel, Premier Lien Chan instructed the 
council to work in coordination with other departments and 
commissions to submit the draft procedures to the Executive Yuan 
for examination and approval as quickly as possible. 
  The draft was supposed to be submitted yesterday. Many 
relevant commissions and departments are opposed to the draft, 
and no consensus was reached after consultations. Suggestions 
have been made for amending the crucial articles of the 
procedures. [words indistinct] 
  (Hsu I-ming) indicated his council will act in accordance 
with the instructions of the Executive Yuan and submit the draft 
procedures for examination and approval after the Spring 
Festival holidays. 

</TEXT>

