<F P=100> North Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Inner Mongolia Announces 1994 Work Targets </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1202080094 Hohhot NEIMENGGU RIBAO in Chinese 22 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> SK1202080094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hohhot NEIMENGGU RIBAO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By correspondent Zheng Yanshi (6774 6056 1395): "The </F>
Standing Committee of the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Regional 
Party Committee Hears Rural and Pastoral Work Report"] 
  [Text] On the arrival of the new year, the regional party 
committee standing committee held a meeting to hear the report 
on agriculture, animal husbandry, and the rural and pastoral 
work prepared by the autonomous regional leading group for rural 
and pastoral work. The meeting comprehensively analyzed the new 
situation and new tasks of the region's agriculture and animal 
husbandry and the rural and pastoral work; fully affirmed the 
achievements in agriculture, animal husbandry, and the rural and 
pastoral work; set forth the 1994 basic tasks and fighting 
targets; arranged the agricultural, livestock, and rural and 
pastoral work; and urged the whole party and all people of the 
region to be mobilized and make concerted efforts to create new 
agricultural and livestock production levels. Wang Qun, 
secretary of the regional party committee; and Wu Liji, Qian 
Fenyong, Bai Enpei, and Wang Zhan, deputy secretaries of the 
regional party committee, made important instructions at the 
meeting. 
  Wang Qun, secretary of the regional party committee, pointed 
out: The cadres and the people across the region should define 
the thinking of welcoming the key year and creating a new 
situation; unswervingly implement the guidelines of the central 
rural work conference, the third plenary session of the 14th 
party Central Committee, and the eighth (enlarged) plenary 
session of the fifth regional party committee; strengthen the 
extent of reform; work out and also implement perfect measures; 
and create a new situation in agriculture, animal husbandry, and 
rural and pastoral work. We should make the rural and pastoral 
work suit the requirements for setting up the socialist market 
economic system; take the market as an orientation and economic 
results as the key; and develop high-yield, good-quality, and 
high-efficient agriculture and animal husbandry. We should 
bring into full play the might of "the primary productive 
forces" and create conditions for science professionals and 
technicians to build agriculture-science-education integrated 
bases in rural and pastoral areas. It is necessary to quicken 
the development of the secondary and tertiary industries and 
promote the pace of becoming fairly well-off. It is necessary 
to continuously implement the measures for reducing peasants and 
herdsmen's burden, safeguard their interests, and mobilize their 
enthusiasm. It is necessary to further support the poor. We 
should adopt special measures to support the peasants and 
herdsmen in the especially poverty-stricken areas and to help 
them eliminate their difficulties. The party committees and 
governments at various levels should strengthen the leadership 
over agriculture, animal husbandry, and the rural and pastoral 
work. All trades and professions and all departments should 
work out perfect measures to support the development of 
agriculture and animal husbandry. All levels should organize 
cadres and send them deep to the forefront of agricultural and 
livestock production, to grasp typical cases, and to conduct 
investigations and study. The leading cadres should adopt the 
forms of handling affairs on the spot to help the grass roots 
and the masses tide over difficulties. We should mobilize the 
forces of the whole party and the whole society and make 
concerted efforts to elevate agriculture, animal husbandry, and 
rural and pastoral work to a new high. 
  In line with the principle of stabilizing agriculture and 
animal husbandry and increasing the income of the peasants and 
the herdsmen and the spirit of "trying every possible means to 
be fast and do more," the meeting defined the 1994 fighting 
targets as follows: We should ensure to turn out 20 billion jin 
of grain and strive to reach 23 billion jin, ensure to produce 
56.6 million head of animals and strive to reach 57 million 
head, ensure to afforest on 5 million mu of land and strive to 
afforest on 5.5 million mu of land, and ensure that the output 
value of town and township enterprises should reach 28 billion 
yuan and strive to have their output value surpass 30 billion 
yuan. The per capita net income of the peasants and the 
herdsmen should increase 100 yuan over 1993. To ensure the 
realization of these targets, we should deepen reform, stabilize 
policies, and strengthen the construction of grass-roots 
organizations, and achieve success in strengthening the 
construction of the agricultural and livestock infrastructural 
facilities, readjusting the economic structures of rural and 
pastoral areas, quickening the development of town and township 
enterprises, and perfecting the socialized service system. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

