<F P=100> Southwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yunnan Border Trade Grows in 1993 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK1402133594 Kunming Yunnan People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1000 GMT 13 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1402133594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kunming Yunnan People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In 1993 the province maintained a vigorous 
development trend in border trade. According to statistics from 
the provincial Border Trade Bureau, last year Yunnan registered 
a total of 2.873 billion yuan in imports and exports through 
border trade, an increase of 26.55 percent over the previous 
year. Last year border trade departments focused their work on 
adjusting the product mix. The imports and exports of bulk 
commodities through border trade developed well. Of commodities 
imported through border trade, 28 categories each exceeded 1 
million yuan, while 16 categories of exported commodities each 
exceeded 10 million yuan, including cigarettes, electrical 
machinery, building materials, and textile products. The 
quality of commodities imported and exported through border 
trade improved as a result of cooperation between the relevant 
management and supervisory departments on both sides. 
  In addition, eight border prefectures have scored marked 
achievements in carrying out economic and technological 
cooperation with Burma, Laos, Vietnam, and Thailand. By the end 
of 1993 they had signed 46 contracts, worth a total of more than 
$100 million. So far contracts worth almost $50 million have 
been completed, 50 percent of the total amount of the province's 
economic and technological cooperation with foreign countries. 

</TEXT>

