<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Public Security Minister Visits Policemen on Duty </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1502005094 Beijing Central Television Program One Network 
in Mandarin 1100 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1502005094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing Central Television Program One Network 
in Mandarin 1100 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "National News Hookup" program] </F>
  [Text] [Video shows Public Security Minister Tao Siju 
talking to a group of officers in front of the Beijing railway 
station and beside a row of fire engines; some unidentified 
officers visiting people in their homes] Public Security 
Minister Tao Siju and other comrades today separately called on 
public security police officers and cadres as well as armed 
police force fire fighters on duty at the Beijing railway 
station, Qianmen, Daxing County, and Beijing municipal fire 
bureau. 
  Tao Siji asked the vast number of public security police 
officers as well as armed police officers and men to stand firm 
at their posts during Spring Festival to safeguard social 
security and prevent fires, so that the people nationwide could 
spend a stable and peaceful festival. 
  In the past few days, relevant leaders of the Ministry of 
Public Security dispatched over a dozen groups of officers to 
various localities nationwide to convey greetings to heroic 
models and family members of public security police who 
sacrificed their lives on duty, and to help them solve their 
problems. 

</TEXT>

