<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shanghai's GNP Rises 22 Percent in January </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK1502054494 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 1318 GMT 
14 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1502054494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, February 14 (CNS) -- An authoritative 
source here has revealed that the value of the gross national 
product (GNP) earned in the city in January this year was RMB 
[renminbi] 14 billion, 22 percent up over the same period of 
last year. This amount showed that the city has continued to 
maintain its rapid economic growth since 1992. 
  According to relevant departments here, the city saw its 
industrial output last month increasing by 20 percent and the 
ratio of production to sales reaching 97 percent. There was an 
even higher growth of turnover of sedans, refrigerators, color 
TV sets and home air-conditioners. The financial revenue 
collected by local governments in the city increased by 110 
percent over the same period of last year and the value of its 
exports by 18 percent. 
  In addition, foreign investment in the city has continued to 
boom with 300 foreign-funded items being approved last month 
with contracted foreign investment of U.S.$550 million. The 
city has also seen 26 financial institutions and 59 
representative offices set up by foreign financial institutions 
in 11 foreign countries and regions. 

</TEXT>

