<H3> <TI>   Tajikistan Reportedly Opposes Use of Force in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1702050794 Beijing XINHUA in English 0222 GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1702050794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, February 16 (XINHUA) -- Tajikistan has 
expressed strong opposition to any use of force in Bosnia. 
  The ITAR-TASS NEWS SERVICE quoted Tajik Foreign Minister 
Rashid Alimov as saying today that any "means of violence" to be 
used to solve the conflict in former Yugoslavia is doomed to 
fail. 
  "Violence will be answered by violence," he said, adding 
that 
no side involved in the Bosnian conflict should cross the "risk 
line" any more. 

</TEXT>

