<F P=100> Near East &amp; South Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Qian Qichen Meets With Pakistan's Bhutto Envoy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1502132894 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Overseas Service in 
English 0800 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1502132894 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Overseas Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Ms. Benazir Bhutto's special envoy, 
Professor N.D. Khan, has held talks in Beijing with the Chinese 
foreign minister, Mr. Qian Qichen, and other leaders on human 
rights abuses by Indian troops in occupied Kashmir. During the 
talks, he delivered a letter from the prime minister for 
President Jiang Zemin. 
  Later, talking to APP [Associated Press of Pakistan] before 
his departure for Tehran, the special envoy said that the letter 
was very specific on human rights violations and atrocities by 
the Indian troops in occupied Kashmir, particularly the 
molestation of women. He said the Kashmir issue was among the 
top priorities of the present government and is the arch-pivot 
of Pakistan's foreign policy. He said that Pakistan intended to 
move a resolution in the third week of this month in Human 
Rights Commission in Geneva on the situation in occupied 
Kashmir. It will express concern on the happenings there. He 
described his talks with Chinese leaders as fruitful and 
constructive. 

</TEXT>

